column1: # The March 1857 reading (the first in the series) has been omitted as it only covers from the 8th onwards.
# The August 1859 reading is described as taken from the Mr Lawton's Hull Manor House Street site, and has been retained.
# British Rainfall gives the location as York Parade on Beverley Road.
# York Parade is the run of buildings on the west side of Beverley Road just north of Trafalgar Street.
# In September 1876 the gauge moved 100 yards north to Fulford House, also on Beverley Road.
